<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-16-0513 </DOCNO><TEXT>The new X-Ray Ordinance will become effective on January 1, 1988 and replacesthe one issued in 1973. Main amendments have been made in the sectionsdealing with the training and qualification of appliers of X-ray equipment,with dose limits, permitted uses in the medical field, and medical controlof persons occupationally exposed to X-radiation. Terms and definitionsof radiation protection have been revised. Completely new items referto the responsibilities of the radiation safety officer. The provisionsconcerning the keeping of records of X-ray applications have been amendedso as to comply with current methods of information processing and handling.</TEXT></DOC>